<p>[Counterpoint: The pursuit of Happiness]â€¨â€¨
BCG Placements Interview (Lost to Karan Jagtiani)</p>

<p>I almost deliberately appeared weak and under confident, instead of telling myself that â€œI can do thisâ€, and then fully immerse myself at the problem, I almost tried to evoke pity of the interviewer. Â Instead of having a supreme faith in my abilities and having my mind 100% on the task at hand: solving the case and communicating my thinking, Â I had part of my mind on appealing to the sympathies of the interviewer.Â Had I been the interviewer, would I have selected myself? Â </p>

